The Banyana Banyana players received a Zoom call earlier on Friday from Ramaphosa. He wished them luck ahead of Saturday’s Women’s Africa Cup of Nations Final (WAFCON) against Morocco. Banyana Banyana square off with Morocco, at the Prince Moulay Abdellah Stadium in Rabat on Saturday, with the aim of winning their first African title. Banyana Banyana has played in three finals without winning yet. Channel Africa's Mosibudi Makhura spoke to Banyana Banyana Head Coach, Desiree Ellis, on The Upside ahead of the final. -- ChannelAfrica/SABCNews--